title: AFL-CIO makes candidate endorsements
maintext:
The Nebraska AFL-CIO endorsed the following local candidates in the May 15 primary election:
Legislature: Matt Hansen, Lincoln (District 26); Patty Pansing Brooks, Lincoln (District 28); Don Schuller, Wymore (District 30).
U.S. House: Dennis P. Crawford, Lincoln (District 1).
Nebraska Board of Regents: Larry Bradley, Omaha (District 4).
State Board of Education: Patricia Timm, Beatrice (District 5).
Public Service Commission: Christa Yoakum, Lincoln (District 1).
Governor: Bob Krist, Omaha.
Secretary of State: Spencer Danner, Omaha.
The group did not make an endorsement in the U.S. Senate race.
The state AFL-CIO is a statewide labor organization representing 23,000 members and 115 local unions and statewide councils.
